            "title": "If statement",
            "id": 126715,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>¿Cómo podemos escribir código que se adapte a diferentes situaciones? Usando la <strong>if statement</strong>.</p><p>Codiamos la palabra clave <code>if</code> para una declaración if.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"if\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"true\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\" {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"print\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Hello!&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"}\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"2\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Hello!\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>if</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "If statement",
            "id": 126716,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>La declaración if <em>ejecuta código</em> solo si el booleano en el que se basa es <code>true</code>. Es como decir, <em>si</em> algo es verdadero, <em>entonces</em> haz esto.</p><p><code>\"Hello!\"</code> se mostrará en la consola si establecemos el valor booleano a <code>true</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"if\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"true\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\" {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"print\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Hello!&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"}\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"3\" endIndex=\"7\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"false\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Hello!\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>true</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "If statement",
            "id": 126717,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Pero, ¿qué pasa si queremos <em>omitir</em> código? Usamos <code>false</code> en su lugar.</p><p>Al establecer el valor en <code>false</code>, evitaremos mostrar <code>\"Hello!\"</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"if\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"false\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\" {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"print\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Hello!&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"}\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"3\" endIndex=\"8\" /></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>false</code>.</p></body></html>"
